<plot>Through the eyes of 11 year old Calvin we see the helplessness and hopelessness that domestic violence inflicts on our children. 'Calvin' depicts a convincing portrait of one of the uglier aspects of contemporary America: and yet there is in it, much lightness, hope and humanity. Race, culture and poverty are all explored in this film. 'Calvin' challenges our assumptions while affirming our love for the underdog and under served.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?091394</url></doc>
